==English==

===Etymology===
First attested in 1597. From {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|absorptiō||a sucking in}}, from {{m|la|absorbeō||absorb}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/əbˈzɔːp.ʃn̩/|/əbˈsɔːp.ʃn̩/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/æbˈsɔɹp.ʃn̩/|/æbˈzɔɹp.ʃn̩/|/əbˈzɔɹp.ʃn̩/|/əbˈsɔɹp.ʃn̩/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-absorption.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The act or process of [[absorbing]] or of being [[absorbed]] as,
## {{context|obsolete|lang=en}} engulfing; swallowing up, as of bodies or land. {{defdate|Attested from the late 16<sup>th</sup> century until the mid 18<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5|page=9}}</ref>
## [[assimilate]]; incorporation. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 18<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
##: ''the '''absorption''' of a smaller tribe into a larger
##: ''the '''absorption''' of bodies in a [[whirlpool]]''
## {{context|chemistry|physics|lang=en}} the [[imbibing]] or [[reception]] by [[molecular]] or chemical action, of [[radiant]] [[energy]]; the process of being [[neutron]]s being absorbed by the [[nucleus]]; [[interception]]. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 18<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
##: ''the '''absorption''' of light, heat, electricity, etc.''
## {{context|physiology|lang=en}} in living organisms, the process by which the materials of growth and [[nutrition]] are absorbed and conveyed to the [[tissue]]s and [[organ]]s; taking in by various means, such as by [[osmosis]]. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 18<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# Entire [[engrossment]] or occupation of the mind. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 19<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
#: '''''absorption''' in some employment''
# Mental assimilation. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 20<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{context|electrical engineering|lang=en}} The retaining of electrical energy for a short time after it has been introduced to the [[dielectric]].
# The taking on of by a shipping company of special charges by another without price increase.
# The natural lessening of radio waves due to atmospheric interference.

